{
  "name": "Impossible Protein Bars",
  "description": "No-bake, grain-free protein bars: whey isolate + collagen + cocoa bound with melted butter and raw honey into a press-in dough, finished with a coconut-oil chocolate shell. Honey is kept as written — it's both the sweetener and the structural binder (the recipe is deliberately free of artificial sweeteners). A no-bake member of the Protein Bars family.",
  "tags": [
    "bars",
    "no-bake",
    "chocolate",
    "high-protein"
  ],
  "yield": {
    "amount": 10,
    "unit": "bars"
  },
  "content": {
    "steps": [
      {
        "componentKey": "d1",
        "order": 1,
        "section": "dough",
        "instructionText": "Combine the whey isolate, collagen, cocoa, and salt. Separately whisk the melted butter, honey, vanilla, and water, then stir into the dry until a thick dough forms. Press firmly into a parchment-lined loaf pan."
      },
      {
        "componentKey": "s1",
        "order": 2,
        "section": "shell",
        "instructionText": "Melt the coconut oil, cocoa, and honey together until smooth and spread over the bars."
      },
      {
        "componentKey": "z1",
        "order": 3,
        "section": "set",
        "instructionText": "Refrigerate until firm, then slice into 10 bars."
      }
    ],
